                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-175" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-175" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-175" type="given" value="JOHN DAVID"></interp>JOHN DAVID ROBERTS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am son-in-law to Mrs. Sarah Brendell, who keeps the Artichoke. The table-cloth is her property—it was taken from a locker in the bar, which communicates with the yard.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner Brown put in a written defence, stating that he found the cloths in the road—and the other prisoners demanding a share, he gave one to Peterson, and as they quarrelled about it, lie threw the other away.)</p>
